  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>sushi rice </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water </strong>for 30 secs (use your hands to wash the grains!) and set aside to drain</p><p>Add the <strong>drained rice</strong>, 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614003601065-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614003601065-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614003601065-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614003601065-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614003601065-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, remove the rice from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving – this is your <strong>sticky rice</strong></p><p>Tip: Don’t peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614003619408-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614003619408-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614003619408-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614003619408-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614003619408-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and set aside to pickle – this is your <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-new--1627636700585-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-new--1627636700585-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-new--1627636700585-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-new--1627636700585-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-new--1627636700585-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), then roughly tear your<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> into the pan and cook for 3 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614003650623-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614003650623-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614003650623-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614003650623-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614003650623-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>cornflour </strong>in 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> [200ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>remaining rice vinegar </strong>in a small bowl – this is your <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p><p>Once the mushrooms have softened, add the <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong> and cook for 2 min further, until a glossy sauce coats the mushrooms</p><p>Once the mushrooms are done, add them to a bowl and set aside, reserve the pan – these are your<strong> sticky teriyaki mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614003672639-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614003672639-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614003672639-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614003672639-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614003672639-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, chop your <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> in half and trim your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> then chop into batons</p><p>Slice each <strong>spring onion baton</strong> into 4 pieces lengthways – this is your <strong>shredded spring onion</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>sugar snap peas </strong>to a pot with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cover with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614003708709-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614003708709-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614003708709-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614003708709-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1614003708709-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>into the pan and cook, covered, for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Tip: Give your egg a little shake before you crack for a perfectly centred yolk!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614003718445-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614003718445-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614003718445-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614003718445-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1614003718445-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>through the<strong> sticky rice</strong> then serve in a bowl</p><p>Top the rice with the <strong>fried egg</strong>,<strong> </strong>then surround it with the <strong>sticky teriyaki mushrooms</strong>, <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong>, <strong>shredded spring onion </strong>and <strong>sugar snap peas</strong></p><p>Pour over any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong> and sprinkle your <strong>shichimi togarashi </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
